rdf:Description.adsbib:abstractText: We present new Chandra and HST data for four gamma-ray blazars selected on the basis of radio morphology with the aim of revealing X-ray and optical emission from their jets at large scales. All the sources have been detected. Spectral energy distributions (SEDs) of the large-scale jets are obtained as well as new X-ray spectra for the blazar cores. Modeling for each object the core (subparsec scale) and large-scale (>~100 kpc) jet SEDs, we derive the properties of the same jet at the two scales. The comparison of speeds and powers at different scales supports a simple scenario for the dynamics and propagation of high-power relativistic jets.
